<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-25T01:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-25T01:35:00-05:00" n="643" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.9112A/3: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-25T10:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">June 25,
                                        1928—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 1:35
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>65. It is my impression that favorable moment exists now to advance
                            proposal to negotiate treaties of arbitration and conciliation with
                            Persian Government, as mentioned in Department’s telegram No. 39, May 8,
                            8 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>